@startuml
title Normal flow (connect -> match -> game over)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam ParticipantPadding 40

participant "PC\n(host side)" as S
participant "CPU\n(custom)" as C

== Boot / liveness check ==
S -> C : PI
note right : PING (periodic;\nboot and liveness check)
C -> S : +PI
note left : PI success response\n(immediate)

== Version query ==
S -> C : VE
C -> S : +VE02MyCPU-v1
note left : 2-digit protocol version\n(currently 02 only) + name\n(ASCII, up to 16 chars)

== Match start (CPU = black, first) ==
S -> C : SB
note right : START BLACK\nrequest the opening move
C -> S : MOf5
note left : CPU plays f5\n(typical black opening;\nstart of Tiger opening)

== Match loop ==
S -> C : MOd6
note right : opponent's move\n(white reply in Tiger opening)
C -> S : MOc3
note left : CPU plays c3\n(Tiger opening, black 3rd)
... alternating per turn ...

== Heartbeat (also during the match) ==
S -> C : PI
C -> S : +PI

... ...

== Game over ==
C -> S : EN
note left : CPU resigns\n(opponent wins)
' or
' S -> C : EB/EW/ED : PC-determined game-over notice

@enduml
